rComments: Took a difficult course and ruined it by spending his time answering off-topic questions, while pacing around the front of the lecture hall. Overkill trying to be funny with constant goat and kale references in all of his examples, and pushes syntax as the only important part of linguistics. I'm among the handful A-level students who dropped.
Great lecturer! Thoroughly engaging and made me love linguistics.
His lectures are amazing, it is important to go but you'll never be bored. Like LIN101, make sure you take tutorial quizzes seriously because they can change your grades drastically sometimes.

rComments: Nick is a fantastic prof. He really cares about his students and even goes the extra mile to provide help on questions outside of course material. He was given an extremely hard course to teach (3rd year syntax) and the textbook was awful, but his notes were clear and detailed and he really did his best in teaching the abstract concepts.
An amazing lecturer! Just listening to him talking can be so funny. Would take him again for sure!
Love him so much, a great professor
He is really chill and understanding. Funny lectures, down to earth professor.
